# Grandmaster at Employment
This is a heuristic problem.

You are given $Q$ queries. 

Below is a setting for case $i$.

There are $N_i$ applicants in an interview queue.

As a human resources specialist, you would like to hire exactly $T_i$ of them and maximize the total value they bring.

You must decide whether to hire the applicant right after the sequential interview that yields their parameters.

Each participant is assessed their competency with $W$ aspects. The aggregate value of a hired team is calculated as $\prod_{k=1}^{W} \sum_{j=1}^{T} A_{i, j, k}$.

Maximize your medium score of all the queries.


## Constraints
- $1 \leq Q \leq 10^5$
- $1 \leq N_i$
- $2 \leq \sum_{i=0}^{Q} N_i \leq 10^5$
- $1 \leq T_i \lt N_i$
- $1 \leq W_i \leq 10$
- $1 \leq A_{i, j, k} \leq 1000$
